50|$|In general, complex metal {{hydrides}} {{have the}} formula MxM'yHn, where M is an alkali metal cation or cation complex and M' is a metal or metalloid. Well known examples feature group 13 elements, especially boron and aluminium including <b>sodium</b> aluminium <b>hydride,</b> NaAlH4 (also known as sodium alanate), lithium aluminum hydride, LiAlH4, and lithium borohydride, (LiBH4). Complex metal hydrides are often soluble in etherial solvents. Other complex metal hydrides are numerous. Illustrative {{examples include the}} salts MgBr(THF)24FeH6 and K2ReH9.|$|R
